article.headline: UC-Santa Barbara 70, Fresno State 42
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Fresno State's unbeaten streak ended Wednesday night as UC Santa Barbara rolled to a 70-42 win. The Gauchos (6-2) held Fresno (7-1) to a season-low 28.3 percent shooting while also forcing 17 turnovers. Chris Devine led Santa Barbara with 19 points, scoring nine in the first nine minutes of the second half as a 10-point halftime lead swelled to 51-30. Alex Harris scored 13 of his 18 points in the first half. Hector Hernandez and Ja'Vance Coleman scored 13 apiece for the Bulldogs.
